value.snippet: Definition of pound. One pound, the international avoirdupois pound, is legally defined as exactly 0.45359237 kilograms. Definition of kilogram. The kilogram (kg) is the SI unit of mass. It is equal to the mass of the international prototype of the kilogram. This prototype is a platinum-iridium international prototype kept at the International Bureau of Weights and Measures.
